description.narrative:
OUTPUTS

a)	Assessment of situation of women and children and availability of supports;
b)	Planning of emergency psychological support for the women and children;
c)	Coordination of activities of NGOs and local administration;
d)	Better interaction and exchange of information among community people and the local administration;
e)	Increased support from international communities for the women and children in the areas;
f)	Improved physical and psychological status of the women and children;
g)	Increased response of the women and children in relief and rehabilitation activities provided for them.

The main objective of the project is to assist the victims among local communities especially the women and children with psychological care and counseling support for their recovery from the traumatic status.  Other specific objectives of the project are:

a)	Provide victim women and children with psychological care and counseling support;
b)	Help community people get support from govt. and other service providing organizations;
c)	Make the local administration informed on the need of psychological counseling and care support of the women and children;
d)	Inspire govt. and other agencies take necessary action to support the women and children with other activities such as shelter, health, education, rehabilitation, advocacy, training, behavioral change communication etc.;
e)	Create sensitization among local community people on the situation of women and children.
